cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper presents a novel type of ensemble Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) model that explicitly learns at multiple scales. The paper focuses on the application of this model to the modeling of biological systems, specifically the prediction of potential energy in a coarse-grained mechanochemical simulation of microtubule bending. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these sub-categories are closely related to machine learning. The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the computational benefits of using Algebraic Multigrid (AMG) literature, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
